00:44:03.484 --> 00:44:04.900
TIMOTHY VERSTYNEN:
Yeah, so that's

00:44:04.900 --> 00:44:07.180
actually another little
side tangent to mine.

00:44:07.180 --> 00:44:10.810
Because the zombieism
that you see in Haitian

00:44:10.810 --> 00:44:14.680
voodoo culture is quite
interesting in that it

00:44:14.680 --> 00:44:17.110
has a proposed
neuropharmacological

00:44:17.110 --> 00:44:18.390
explanation.

00:44:18.390 --> 00:44:21.060
So there's a classic
book by Wade Davis, who

00:44:21.060 --> 00:44:24.200
was an ethnobotanist,
who went down to Haiti

00:44:24.200 --> 00:44:27.610
and made two particular
pharmacological links

00:44:27.610 --> 00:44:28.840
to Haitian zombies.

00:44:28.840 --> 00:44:31.540
And one was
tetrodotoxin, which was

00:44:31.540 --> 00:44:33.730
the poison used
to simulate death.

00:44:33.730 --> 00:44:36.690
And tetrodotoxin works by
blocking the sodium channels

00:44:36.690 --> 00:44:39.830
that allow neurons to fire in
the peripheral nervous system.

00:44:39.830 --> 00:44:42.340
So your muscles
become paralyzed.

00:44:42.340 --> 00:44:46.150
And it actually won't kill
you unless your diaphragm

00:44:46.150 --> 00:44:47.430
stops working.

00:44:47.430 --> 00:44:49.760
So basically, it kills you
because the diaphragm muscle

00:44:49.760 --> 00:44:50.343
stops working.

00:44:50.343 --> 00:44:53.180
But if you get a low
enough dose, what'll happen

00:44:53.180 --> 00:44:56.460
is that your diaphragm will
keep moving so slowly that you

00:44:56.460 --> 00:44:57.640
can't really detect it.

00:44:57.640 --> 00:45:00.050
But in all intents and
purposes, you look dead.

00:45:00.050 --> 00:45:01.300
So that's the simulated death.

00:45:01.300 --> 00:45:03.560
And then the control
aspects, he proposed

00:45:03.560 --> 00:45:11.610
that the bokors, who are the
bad or evil voodoo priests,

00:45:11.610 --> 00:45:14.925
would dose the individual after
the tetrodotoxin had worn off

00:45:14.925 --> 00:45:16.660
when they dug them
out of their grave

00:45:16.660 --> 00:45:19.900
that they were buried
alive in, would douse them

00:45:19.900 --> 00:45:23.010
with datura, which has
three major psychoactive

00:45:23.010 --> 00:45:26.670
ingredients, [? hyoscapines ?],
scopolamine, and atropine,

00:45:26.670 --> 00:45:27.810
I think.

00:45:27.810 --> 00:45:30.994
Each one of those will
induce a psychotic state.

00:45:30.994 --> 00:45:33.160
And so the idea is that you
can make this person who

00:45:33.160 --> 00:45:37.197
is now convinced this he's dead,
because he saw himself dead.

00:45:37.197 --> 00:45:39.530
He was well aware of everything
that's happening to him,

00:45:39.530 --> 00:45:40.810
felt buried.

00:45:40.810 --> 00:45:41.970
And then he gets raised.

00:45:41.970 --> 00:45:44.010
And then there's a
psychoactive chemical

00:45:44.010 --> 00:45:45.190
that keeps him compliant.

00:45:45.190 --> 00:45:46.549
That was the Wade Davis theory.

00:45:46.549 --> 00:45:47.340
It's controversial.

00:45:47.340 --> 00:45:48.710
It hasn't been replicated yet.

00:45:48.710 --> 00:45:51.570
And people are saying that
there's probably other aspects

00:45:51.570 --> 00:45:54.340
to it that link more to
psychological belief.

00:45:54.340 --> 00:45:57.730
But yeah, the Haitian voodoo
zombie links to neurobiology

00:45:57.730 --> 00:45:59.030
are quite interesting that way.

