00:53:34.186 --> 00:53:37.100
AUDIENCE: So one connection
that you didn't touch on

00:53:37.100 --> 00:53:39.740
is between rabies and zombieism.

00:53:39.740 --> 00:53:41.430
I've heard people
talk about that.

00:53:41.430 --> 00:53:44.890
Any comments on whether rabies
would be or a form of rabies--

00:53:44.890 --> 00:53:47.290
TIMOTHY VERSTYNEN: So a
longer version of the talk,

00:53:47.290 --> 00:53:48.380
we actually go over this.

00:53:48.380 --> 00:53:51.840
Because when we go over the
memory systems and the impulse

00:53:51.840 --> 00:53:54.550
control systems, those
are all linked up

00:53:54.550 --> 00:53:57.630
to a system known as
the Papez circuit.

00:53:57.630 --> 00:53:59.570
That's a classic
neurological circuit

00:53:59.570 --> 00:54:02.510
that was discovered
in the 1930s.

00:54:02.510 --> 00:54:05.300
And it was discovered
using the rabies virus.

00:54:05.300 --> 00:54:07.200
And so what this guy
James Papez would do

00:54:07.200 --> 00:54:09.241
is he was trying to find
the link between emotion

00:54:09.241 --> 00:54:09.930
and intention.

00:54:09.930 --> 00:54:12.974
How is it that we can't remember
what we did at the store

00:54:12.974 --> 00:54:14.390
yesterday, but
everybody remembers

00:54:14.390 --> 00:54:15.560
where they were at 9/11?

00:54:15.560 --> 00:54:19.300
How do we have these
emotional bonding of memories?

00:54:19.300 --> 00:54:21.950
And so he mapped out
this theoretical circuit

00:54:21.950 --> 00:54:24.630
and then would map it out in
cats by injecting the rabies

00:54:24.630 --> 00:54:26.649
virus and watching the
virus propagate from one

00:54:26.649 --> 00:54:28.440
area to the next, look
for the connections.

00:54:28.440 --> 00:54:32.530
And he actually made cats
that were memory problems.

00:54:32.530 --> 00:54:34.630
They were hyperaggressive.

00:54:34.630 --> 00:54:36.590
So we do a tongue in
cheek thing saying

00:54:36.590 --> 00:54:40.130
that James Papez made
the first zombie cats.

00:54:40.130 --> 00:54:44.800
But the rabies virus is a very
specific type of infection.

00:54:44.800 --> 00:54:47.260
And it's very general.

00:54:47.260 --> 00:54:51.440
So what it does is it
attacks a particular cell,

00:54:51.440 --> 00:54:53.710
jumps across what's known
as the synapse, which

00:54:53.710 --> 00:54:57.122
is the gap between cells,
and keeps propagating down

00:54:57.122 --> 00:54:57.830
to the next cell.

00:54:57.830 --> 00:54:58.870
And it just wanders.

00:54:58.870 --> 00:55:01.074
It just follows
from place to place.

00:55:01.074 --> 00:55:03.240
So if you get an infection
in one part of the brain,

00:55:03.240 --> 00:55:05.657
it's-- where it goes
is determined by who

00:55:05.657 --> 00:55:06.490
it's connected with.

00:55:06.490 --> 00:55:08.790
And it'll keep traveling
until it basically

00:55:08.790 --> 00:55:11.190
kills the organism.

00:55:11.190 --> 00:55:13.250
Now, normally you
get some symptoms

00:55:13.250 --> 00:55:16.560
like the cognitive disorders.

00:55:16.560 --> 00:55:20.210
You'll get delusions and
dementia with rabies infection.

00:55:20.210 --> 00:55:22.820
You get hydrophobia.

00:55:22.820 --> 00:55:25.610
So individuals infected
with the rabies virus

00:55:25.610 --> 00:55:26.792
will be afraid of water.

00:55:26.792 --> 00:55:27.500
They won't drink.

00:55:27.500 --> 00:55:29.260
They'll become dehydrated.

00:55:29.260 --> 00:55:33.970
And some of those are
explained by the virus

00:55:33.970 --> 00:55:36.490
doesn't survive well when
there's lots of brain swelling.

00:55:36.490 --> 00:55:39.360
So it automatically
dehydrates you

00:55:39.360 --> 00:55:41.820
to keep that brain
swelling down.

00:55:41.820 --> 00:55:43.500
Things like that
have been put forth

00:55:43.500 --> 00:55:45.750
as explanations for
those kind of behaviors.

00:55:45.750 --> 00:55:47.630
But a lot of them
just happen to be--

00:55:47.630 --> 00:55:50.460
people show those when the
virus has spread so far

00:55:50.460 --> 00:55:52.900
throughout the brain as
to basically wipe away

00:55:52.900 --> 00:55:54.460
most of the neocortex.

00:55:54.460 --> 00:55:57.986
And so it's nonspecific in the
sense of where it's attacking.

00:55:57.986 --> 00:55:59.610
But we really start
to see the symptoms

00:55:59.610 --> 00:56:03.320
once it's just so widespread
as to be catastrophic.

00:56:03.320 --> 00:56:06.450
So yeah, the rabies
virus has been

00:56:06.450 --> 00:56:10.120
linked to zombies more
times than anything else.

